AlmenaraGames.​MultiAudioManager
MonoBehaviour
public
AlmenaraGames.​MultiAudioManager

The Multi Audio Manager contains a variety of methods for play and manage the sounds according to your needs and is the one that initializes the system using a singleton.

Types
UpdateModes
public enum UpdateModes

ScaledTime,

UnscaledTime

Properties
Paused
public static bool Paused { get; set }

Sets the paused state of the audio system.

If set to true, all Multi Audio Sources playing will be paused.

This works in the same way as pausing the game in the editor. While the pause-state is true, the AudioSettings.dspTime will be frozen and further Multi Audio Sources play requests will start off paused.

If you want certain sounds to still play during the pause, you need to set the IgnoreListenerPause property on the Multi Audio Sources to true for these.

This is typically menu item sounds or background music for the menu.
